; Banjaji's Realistic bodily needs 

; Hunger
; 1 unit of eat_satiety equals 20 000 kcal. 
; Used this as a reference: https://www.nhs.uk/live-well/healthy-weight/managing-your-weight/calorie-checker/

; Thirst
; 1 unit of eat_thirstiness is equivalent of 1 kg of water.
; With normal diet 25% of water intake comes from food. (https://doi.org/10.3390/nu8100630)
; Food doesn't dehydrate. Your mouth may dry when you eat crackers but in your whole body 
; nothing changes or you even gain water. Think about eating cucumbers and extrapolate to sausages.
; Took values from here: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1753-4887.2010.00304.x but considered dried state.
; Diarrhea increases amount of shit (exess water) from 0 to 1400 g depending on severity (https://sci-hub.se/https://doi.org/10.1016/j.gtc.2012.06.006).
; Weak diarrhea = 300 g, medium diarrhea = 600 g, strong diarrhea = 1000 g

